reserve z for (Element of X);
theorem
Th21: (I is (p-ideal of X) iff (for x holds (for y holds ((x in I & x <= y) implies y in I))))
proof
thus (I is (p-ideal of X) implies (for x holds (for y holds ((x in I & x <= y) implies y in I))))
proof
assume I is (p-ideal of X);
then A1: ( BCK-part X ) c= I by CKB25:1;
let x;
let y;
assume that
A2: x in I
and
A3: x <= y;
A4: ( x \ y ) = ( 0. X ) by A3,BCIALG_1:def 11;
then ( ( y \ x ) ` ) = ( x \ y ) by BCIALG_1:6;
then ( 0. X ) <= ( y \ x ) by A4,BCIALG_1:def 11;
then ( y \ x ) in ( BCK-part X );
hence thesis by A2,A1,BCIALG_1:def 18;
end;

assume A5: (for x holds (for y holds ((x in I & x <= y) implies y in I)));
A6: (for x holds (for y holds (for z holds ((( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I & y in I) implies x in I))))
proof
let x;
let y;
let z;
assume that
A7: ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) in I
and
A8: y in I;
( ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) \ ( x \ y ) ) = ( 0. X ) by BCIALG_1:def 3;
then ( ( x \ z ) \ ( y \ z ) ) <= ( x \ y ) by BCIALG_1:def 11;
then ( x \ y ) in I by A5,A7;
hence thesis by A8,BCIALG_1:def 18;
end;
( 0. X ) in I by BCIALG_1:def 18;
hence thesis by A6,CKB23:def 1;
end;
